headline: Siemens Energy Closes The Book On 2025 Amid 'Unprecedented Demand' For Gas Turbines
summary: Siemens Energy reported fiscal fourth-quarter earnings and revenue before Friday's stock market opens closing the book on fiscal 2025 and a year marked by strong demand for gas turbines amid expected increases in the need for electricity and the AI data center boom.  Siemens Energy also reported a net profit of 236 million euros ($274.6 million) compared with a loss of 254 million euros a year ago.  Siemens Energy added that will look to achieve compound annual revenue growth in the low-teens percentage range through 2028.
